## Python lists
Python lists are used to store multiple data items in a single variable. Lists are objects that store an array of data
using an index structure that can be referenced based on a numerical structure from 0.

List properties
• Ordered
• Mutable
• Allows duplicates
• Indexed

## List example
mycars = ["BMW", "Mercedes", "Audi", "Lexus"]   
print(mycars)

## Python dictionaries
Python dictionaries are used to store data values in key:value pairs. 
Unlike lists, dictionaries have a much more rigid structure where values are not indexed based on a numerical structure. 
Instead, data values are accessed by referencing the associated user defined key.

## Dictionary properties
• Ordered
• Mutable
• Duplicates are not allowed

## Dictionary example
cardict = {
  "brand": "BMW", 
  "model": "X5", 
  "year": 2020
  }
print(cardict)
#output: {'brand': 'BMW', 'model': 'X5', 'year': 2020}
